    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-10-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-10-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="829"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d829">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/5427: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Viborg</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Imbrie</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Viborg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 20, 1919</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received 2:22 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>122. Fighting now in progress at Putiloffski works in outskirts of Petrograd.
                    Bolsheviks evidently intend to defend city. Reported railroad between Petrograd
                    and Moscow is cut leaving Vologda railroad sole egress from city. Newspapers
                    have ceased publication. Red Army still obstruct [<hi rend="italic">on</hi>]
                    Finnish border.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Imbrie</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
